reviews.text: Have been here for afternoon tea since I was small. It's a chill little restaurant, with classy background music and not much lighting. Really love the atmosphere there. The price of the afternoon tea is the most reasonable compared to lunch and dinner. Good service.
Very good for the price. 108$ for soup with delicious focaccia, chicken with mozzarella and a soft drink. Music taste could be improved though

A very non-described "western" style restaurant on a North Point back street. Food to be fair is acceptable but tables are tightly placed together.  Expect to pay a little over $100 per head for lunch, & around $200 for dinner.
Very decent Sunday brunch in a nice, quiet environment, at reasonable cost.
Elegance place, delicious food and reason price

reviews.text: Have been here for afternoon tea since I was small. It's a chill little restaurant, with classy background music and not much lighting. Really love the atmosphere there. The price of the afternoon tea is the most reasonable compared to lunch and dinner. Good service.
扖類不錯，但意粉超乾好難食。另外，同行友人的木盤上全是活蟻，起碼10隻以上。好污糟!!
抵食美味既西餐，西餐款式又多，經常都有驚喜，餐廳入面裝修氣氛都唔錯，如果多人建議先打去訂位
食物質素降，提不起意欲光顧
Very good for the price. 108$ for soup with delicious focaccia, chicken with mozzarella and a soft drink. Music taste could be improved though
